<p>&#8216;A British resident stranded in Jamaica with her baby, who was told by the Home Office the boy could not come to the UK because he had an “established life” on the Caribbean island, has now been told by the Home Office that she can bring him, after the Guardian exposed the family’s plight.&#8217;</p>
<p><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2022/jul/12/home-office-grants-woman-and-baby-stranded-in-jamaica-leave-to-return-to-uk">Full Story</a></p><p>The Guardian, 12th July 2022</p><p>Source: <a href="https://www.theguardian.com">www.theguardian.com</a></p>